  "text": "To account for scale effects in the dynamic model, two approaches exist. If prior knowledge of the variation of c s,⌬ with scale is available, the parameter ␤ can be prescribed a priori. Such a \"semi-dynamic\" approach with an imposed parameter ␤ was tested by Meneveau and Lund [CITATION_1] to capture scale dependence in the transition from LES to direct numerical simulation ͑DNS͒ ͑⌬ → the Kolmogorov scale ͒ for finely resolved LES. The approach was also used in simulations by Bou-Zeid et al. [CITATION_2] for wall-bounded flows in the limit where ⌬ tends to the local integral scale near the wall. In both studies, the semi-dynamic scale-dependent model was shown to give better results than the scale-invariant model.",
